metadata.description: The righteous and rigorous Dandelion Knight, and Acting Grand Master of Mondstadt's Knights of Favonius.
metadata.title: Dandelion Knight

metadata.description: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.
The languid but knowledgeable Librarian of the Knights of Favonius, deemed by Sumeru Academia to be their most distinguished graduate in the past two centuries.
metadata.title: Witch of Purple Rose

metadata.description: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.
Every citizen of Mondstadt adores Barbara. She learned the word "idol" from a magazine.
metadata.title: Shining Idol

metadata.description: An accomplished swordsman and a strategic thinker in the Knights of Favonius, rumored to hail from beyond Mondstadt.
metadata.title: Frostwind Swordsman

metadata.description: The tycoon of a winery empire in Mondstadt, unmatched in every possible way.
metadata.title: The Dark Side of Dawn

metadata.description: A boy who lives among the wolves in Wolvendom of Mondstadt, away from human civilization. As agile as lightning.
metadata.title: Wolf Boy

metadata.description: Always energetic and full of life, Amber's the best — albeit only — Outrider of the Knights of Favonius.
metadata.title: Gliding Champion

metadata.description: One of the many bards of Mondstadt, who freely wanders the city's streets and alleys.
metadata.title: Windborne Bard

metadata.description: A renowned chef from Liyue. She's extremely passionate about cooking and excels at making her signature hot and spicy dishes.
metadata.title: Exquisite Delicacy

metadata.description: Captain of her crew, The Crux. She's quite an unbound and forthright woman.
metadata.title: Uncrowned Lord of the Ocean

metadata.description: A young man carrying a longsword who is frequently seen at book booths. He has a chivalrous heart and yearns for justice and fairness for all.
metadata.title: Juvenile Galant

metadata.description: A yaksha adeptus who defends Liyue. Also heralded as the "Conqueror of Demons" and "Vigilant Yaksha."
metadata.title: Vigilant Yaksha

metadata.description: The Tianquan of the Liyue Qixing. Her wealth is unsurpassed in all of Teyvat.
metadata.title: Eclipsing Star

metadata.description: An explosives expert and a regular at the Knights of Favonius's confinement room. Also known as Fleeing Sunlight.
metadata.title: Fleeing Sunlight

metadata.description: A mysterious expert contracted by the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor. Extremely knowledgeable in all things.
metadata.title: Vago Mundo

metadata.cvJapanese: 内田真礼 & 増谷康紀
metadata.description: A mysterious girl who calls herself "Prinzessin der Verurteilung" and travels with a night raven named Oz.
metadata.title: Prinzessin der Verurteilung!

metadata.description: A good-natured adventurer from Mondstadt who's unfortunately extremely unlucky.
metadata.title: Trial by Fire

metadata.description: No. 11 of The Harbingers, also known as "Childe." His name is highly feared on the battlefield.
metadata.title: Childe

metadata.description: A maid who faithfully serves the Knights of Favonius. She dreams of joining their ranks someday.
metadata.title: Chivalric Blossom

metadata.description: An apprentice and herb gatherer at Bubu Pharmacy. An undead with a bone-white complexion, she seldom has much in the way of words or emotion.
metadata.title: Icy Resurrection

metadata.description: A young exorcist from a family of exorcists. He does everything he can to suppress his abundance of yang energy.
metadata.title: Frozen Ardor

metadata.description: The secretary at Yuehai Pavilion. The blood of the qilin, an illuminated beast, flows within her veins.
metadata.title: Plenilune Gaze

metadata.description: A genius known as the Kreideprinz, he is the Chief Alchemist and Captain of the Investigation Team of the Knights of Favonius.
metadata.title: Kreideprinz

metadata.description: A young lady who has inherited trace amounts of non-human blood. She is the incredibly popular bartender of the Cat's Tail tavern.
metadata.title: Kätzlein Cocktail

metadata.description: A mysterious young astrologer who proclaims herself to be "Astrologist Mona Megistus," and who possesses abilities to match the title. Erudite, but prideful.
metadata.title: Astral Reflection

metadata.description: The Yuheng of the Liyue Qixing. Keqing has much to say about Rex Lapis's unilateral approach to policymaking in Liyue — but in truth, gods admire skeptics such as her quite a lot.
metadata.title: Driving Thunder

metadata.description: An alchemist filled with curiosity about all things. She researches bio-alchemy.
metadata.title: Harmless Sweetie

metadata.description: Liyue's sole rock 'n' roll musician. She rebels against ossified prejudices using her music and passionate singing.
metadata.title: Blazing Riff

metadata.description: A sister of the church, though you wouldn't know it if it weren't for her attire. Known for her sharp, cold words and manner, she often works alone.
metadata.title: Thorny Benevolence

metadata.description: The 77th Director of the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor. She took over the business at a rather young age.
metadata.title: Fragrance in Thaw

metadata.description: A well-known legal adviser active in Liyue Harbor. A brilliant young lady in whose veins runs the blood of an illuminated beast.
metadata.title: Wise Innocence

metadata.description: The Spindrift Knight, a scion of the old aristocracy, and the Captain of the Knights of Favonius Reconnaissance Company. The reason for which a descendant of the ancient nobles might join the Knights remains a great mystery in Mondstadt to this very day.
metadata.title: Dance of the Shimmering Wave
